Class PersistentBean

public class PersistentBean
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable

A basic bean for persistence, that provides a unique ID and matching equals() and hashCode() methods.

findOrCreate

public static <T extends PersistentBean> T findOrCreate(java.lang.Class<T> beanType,
                                                        java.lang.String id)
Tries to fetch an object of type beanType with specified id from database (using Ebean). If no such object is found, a new one is created and it's id property set to the specified id. This newly created object is _not_ saved to the database. You can detect wether an object is new or came from the database via isPersisted()

Parameters:
beanType -
id -
Returns:
an object of class beanType; never null.
